      "content": "hey i'm working on this custom loss function for my research and it's tripping me up. it's a Sparsity-Aware Cross-Entropy loss. basically it needs to penalize non-zero entries in a mask tensor while calculating the standard cross entropy.\n\ni need the implementation for `SparsityLoss` to inherit from `torch.nn.Module`. \n\nhere's the test case i'm trying to pass:\n\n```python\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\n\nclass SparsityLoss(nn.Module):\n    # implementation goes here\n    pass\n\ndef test_sparsity_loss():\n    criterion = SparsityLoss(sparsity_weight=0.5)\n    logits = torch.tensor([[1.0, 2.0, 0.5], [0.5, 1.0, 2.0]], requires_grad=True)\n    targets = torch.tensor([1, 2])\n    mask = torch.tensor([[1.0, 0.0, 1.0], [0.0, 1.0, 1.0]])\n    \n    loss = criterion(logits, targets, mask)\n    \n    # expected value calculated manually for this specific setup\n    expected_loss = torch.tensor(1.3452) \n    \n    assert torch.allclose(loss, expected_loss, atol=1e-4), f\"Expected {expected_loss}, got {loss}\"\n    print(\"Test passed!\")\n\ntest_sparsity_loss()\n```\n\ncan u write the class for me? it needs to work with these exact inputs to match my math.",
